        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "On release 20145 ( 2010-01-08 ) the comments are always striped with the follow sintax:\r\n{code:title=Line 215} \r\n$valueCopy = preg_replace('#<!--(?:[^<]+|<(?!\\!--))*?(--\\s*>)#us', '', (string) $value);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis make string with parts like \"Rol\u00f4\", \"harm\u00f4nicas\" became null, so I really needed to returned the old way in *stable* services.\r\n{code:title=Old Way}\r\n    \/\/ If comments are allowed, then replace them with unique identifiers\r\n    if ($this->getCommentsAllowed()) {\r\n    preg_match_all('\/<\\!--.*?--\\s*>\/s' , (string) $valueCopy, $matches);\r\n    $comments = array_unique($matches[0]);\r\n    foreach ($comments as $k => $v) {\r\n        $valueCopy = str_replace($v, self::UNIQUE_ID_PREFIX . $k, $valueCopy);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code}"
        },
