        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37718",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Comments are always stripped because they are potential unsecure.\r\n\r\nTo prevent code injection these are no longer allowed with the actual releases and will not be implemented again.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T06:13:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T06:13:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37724",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thomas -- the problem is that non-commented strings are being stripped. I suspect this is due to using the \"u\" unicode flag on the regex, which isn't really needed in this particular case.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T07:13:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T07:13:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37725",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please test the above patch (use \"patch -p1 < strip_tags.patch\" from your root directory), and let me know if it resolves the issue. I also need to run it by others on our security team.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T07:16:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T07:16:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37726",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bladed",
                        "name": "bladed",
                        "displayName": "Stephan \"Bladed\" de Souza",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The patch works great.\r\n\r\nThanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bladed",
                        "name": "bladed",
                        "displayName": "Stephan \"Bladed\" de Souza",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T07:36:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T07:36:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37727",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Matthew:\r\nI don't think that this is the real problem.\r\nI think that in Stephans environment unicode support is disabled.\r\nBecause ISO-8859-1 characters are a sub-table of unicode but not reverse.\r\n\r\nThis means that we need to select between two cases:\r\n 1. Unicode enabled\r\nand\r\n 2. Unicode disabled\r\n\r\nWe need to seperate this stripping logic within 2 calls. One for unicode and one for non-unicode.\r\n\r\nSee the Alnum filter for details about what I mean.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T08:15:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T08:15:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37728",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bladed",
                        "name": "bladed",
                        "displayName": "Stephan \"Bladed\" de Souza",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thomas:\r\n\r\nTried with Alnum unicode test:\r\n{code}\r\n(@preg_match('\/\\pL\/u', 'a')) ? true : false;\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nWindows Server w\/ Apache 2.2 + PHP5.2.11: true\r\nFreeBSD w\/ Apache 2.2 + PHP5.2.11: true",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bladed",
                        "name": "bladed",
                        "displayName": "Stephan \"Bladed\" de Souza",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T08:30:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T08:30:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37729",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Interesting because I am myself on Windows but with unicode and have no problems on ISO encoded chars.\r\n\r\nTherefor I thought that you may have disabled unicode in your environment.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T08:40:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T08:40:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37739",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "At last I was able to reproduce this behaviour.\r\nThanks for the patch.\r\n\r\nFixed with r20315",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T15:09:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T15:09:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37751",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thomas, please revert the patch. I'm waiting for feedback from Paddy, who reported the original security vulnerability; I don't want to re-introduce a security issue.",
